<TITLE> Tax holiday for power savers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 11 (bdnews24.com)  The Awami League-led coalition government's second budget aims to conserve energy and encourage use of renewable energy. The national budget, presented by AMA Muhith in the parliament on Thursday, proposes to provide tax holiday for industries manufacturing solar panels and energy-saving bulbs. It also proposed similar facilities for contraceptives producers. In a bid to spur investment in heavy industries, a VAT exemption has been proposed for manufacturers of refrigerators, freezers, motorcycles for four years to protect local industries and to provide incentives to manufacturers instead of assemblers. Muhith was, however, skeptic towards tax holiday in his last budget. Despite repeated demands from business quarters, the finance minister refused to extend tax holiday facilities to certain sectors, particularly textiles, in the current budget. Tax holidays act as an impediment to the taxpaying culture, Muhith said in his last budget
